claim.claim-text:
1. A shearing apparatus for cutting tires comprising:
a frame;
a shearing assembly configured to shear a portion of a tire along a shear plane, the shearing assembly including a lower shear blade structure and an upper shear blade structure mounted on the frame in a shearing relationship with the lower shear blade structure;
a thrust adjustment assembly including a thrust plate support mounted in fixed relation to the frame and a thrust plate mounted adjustably on the thrust plate support, wherein the thrust adjustment assembly is configured to press against the upper shear blade structure as the upper shear blade structure moves toward the shear position in an adjustable manner to adjust a proximity of the upper shear blade structure to the lower shear blade structure in the shear position; and
a tire indexing structure configured to advance a portion of the tire a distance through the shear plane for shearing the portion of the tire at the shear plane away from a remainder of the tire, the tire indexing structure including:
a tire clamping assembly configured to clamp onto a location on the tire and being movable between an initial position and a final position to move the portion of the tire through the shear plane;
a carriage assembly configured to move the tire clamping assembly between the initial position and the final position;
and a guide defining a path along which the carriage assembly and tire clamping assembly is movable between the initial and final positions.

11. A shearing apparatus for cutting tires comprising:
a frame;
a shearing assembly configured to shear a portion of a tire along a shear plane, the shearing assembly including a lower shear blade structure and an upper shear blade structure mounted on the frame in a shearing relationship with the lower shear blade structure, the upper shearing blade structure being movable with respect to the lower shearing blade structure between an open position and a shear position;
wherein the lower shear blade structure includes a lower shear blade with a lower shear blade surface, and the upper shear blade structure includes an upper shear blade with art upper shear blade surface, and a plane of the upper shear blade surface is parallel to a plane of the lower shear blade surface such that the shear surfaces are in abutment when the upper and lower shear structures are in the shear position; and
a thrust adjustment assembly including a thrust plate support mounted in fixed relation to the frame and a thrust plate mounted adjustably on the thrust plate support, wherein the thrust adjustment assembly is configured to press against the upper shear blade structure as the upper shear blade structure moves toward the shear position in an adjustable manner to adjust a proximity of the upper shear blade structure to the lower shear blade structure in the shear position.

12. A shearing apparatus for cutting tires comprising:
a frame;
a shearing assembly configured to shear a portion of a tire along a shear plane, the shearing assembly including a lower shear blade structure and an upper shear blade structure mounted on the frame in a shearing relationship with the lower shear blade structure, the upper shearing blade structure being movable with respect to the lower shearing blade structure between an open position and a shear position;
wherein the lower shear blade structure includes a lower shear blade with a lower shear blade edge, and the upper shear blade structure includes an upper shear blade with an upper shear blade edge; and
wherein the upper shear blade structure includes an upper grip element configured to grip a tire positioned between the upper and lower shear blade structures wherein the upper shear blade structure moves toward the lower shear blade structure, the upper grip element having a lower edge contoured to grip a tire positioned between the upper and lower shear blade structures, the upper grip element being mounted on the upper blade support arm adjacent to the upper shear blade, the lower edge having a plurality of arcuate divots formed therein; and
a thrust adjustment assembly including a thrust plate support mounted in fixed relation to the frame and a thrust plate mounted adjustably on the thrust plate support, wherein the thrust adjustment assembly is configured to press against the upper shear blade structure as the upper shear blade structure moves toward the shear position in an adjustable manner to adjust a proximity of the upper shear blade structure to the lower shear blade structure in the shear position.
